@logic-eval text
Use logic-eval for bounded symbolic reasoning that benefits from explicit formalization rather than arbitrary code.
Prefer it for graph, path, reachability, ordering, constraint, search, finite rule, and bounded numeric problems, plus small legacy use/when/then guards that remain worth keeping as compatibility shorthand.
The body may be a natural-language problem statement, or a JSON envelope with explicit program_steps when exact control is needed.
Prefer result_mode structured when a downstream step needs machine-readable output, then let writerLLM or template-eval handle user-facing prose.
Avoid logic-eval for memo writing, open-ended explanation, arbitrary scripting, or vague requests that cannot be bounded honestly.
